headline: Are Lockheed Shares Attractive as Pentagon Pushes Missile Makers to Double Production?
summary: Thinking about what to do with Lockheed Martin stock? You are not alone. For anyone watching this legendary defense contractor, the action has been anything but dull, especially lately. Over the past month, shares have climbed 4.7%, a noticeable rebound after a 2.0% dip just a week earlier. Yet in the bigger picture, Lockheed Martin is still down 16.8% over the past year, reflecting both ongoing sector challenges and rapidly shifting investor expectations about defense spending and risks...
